    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>General Description</title>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Function</title>
          <para>The radome interface connects the BH-STA350 bulkhead to the forward sensor bay. It provides mechanical support and electromagnetic sealing for active sensor systems.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Design Features</title>
          <para>The interface includes a 10-hole radial fastener pattern, EMI gaskets, and thermal isolation pads. It is designed to accommodate radar AESA, GNSS, and SATCOM payloads.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Integration</title>
          <para>The radome interface is mounted directly onto Frame C0 and aligns with the firewall layer. It includes provisions for cable routing and sensor calibration access.</para>
        </levelledPara>

        <levelledPara>
          <title>Compliance</title>
          <para>The interface meets DO-160G requirements for EMI shielding and thermal dissipation. It is validated under the COMPARTMENT_BOUNDARY_VERIFIED badge.</para>
        </levelledPara>

      </levelledPara>
    </description>
